<item>
            <title>[LU-3098] failure to auto trigger paused LFSCK causes mount to fail on slave MDTs</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3098</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;After 7e915f5d, in mdt_prepare() if the OBD_IOC_START_LFSCK ioctl() fails and mdt-&amp;gt;mdt_seq_site.ss_node_id != 0 then the MDT will fail to mount.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;static int mdt_prepare(const struct lu_env *env,
                struct lu_device *pdev,
                struct lu_device *cdev)
{
	...

	rc = mdt-&amp;gt;mdt_child-&amp;gt;md_ops-&amp;gt;mdo_iocontrol(env, mdt-&amp;gt;mdt_child,
                                                   OBD_IOC_START_LFSCK,
                                                   0, NULL);
        if (rc != 0)
                CWARN(&quot;Fail to auto trigger paused LFSCK.\n&quot;);

	if (mdt-&amp;gt;mdt_seq_site.ss_node_id == 0) {
                rc = mdt-&amp;gt;mdt_child-&amp;gt;md_ops-&amp;gt;mdo_root_get(env, mdt-&amp;gt;mdt_child, &amp;amp;mdt-&amp;gt;mdt_md_root_fid);
                if (rc)
                        RETURN(rc);
        }

        ...
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If this is really the intended behavior (I assume not) then the CWARN() should be upgraded to CERROR().&lt;/p&gt;</description>
